# 📊 HR Workforce Analytics Dashboard

## 📌 Project Overview

This project demonstrates an end-to-end HR analytics workflow using **Python, SQL, and Power BI**. The dataset was cleaned and preprocessed in Python, analyzed using SQL, and transformed into an interactive Power BI dashboard to provide actionable insights into employee distribution, salaries, performance, experience, hiring trends, and work modes.

---

## 🎯 Project Objectives

* Clean and preprocess HR employee data using Python.
* Perform business analysis using SQL queries.
* Build an interactive Power BI dashboard.
* Analyze workforce trends across departments, locations, and work modes.
* Generate insights to support HR decision-making.

---

## 🛠️ Tools & Technologies

* **Python (Pandas, NumPy)**
* **Matplotlib & Seaborn**
* **SQL (MySQL)**
* **Power BI**
* **Power Query**
* **DAX**

---

## 📂 Dataset

The dataset contains the following fields:

* Employee_ID
* Full_Name
* Department
* Job_Title
* Hire_Date
* Hire_Year
* Location
* Performance_Rating
* Experience_Years
* Status
* Work_Mode
* Salary_INR

---

## 🧹 Data Cleaning (Python)

* Removed duplicate records.
* Handled missing values.
* Standardized categorical values.
* Converted data types.
* Formatted date columns.
* Performed exploratory data analysis (EDA) and created visualizations.

---

## 🗄️ SQL Analysis

The following business queries were performed:

* Retrieved complete employee records.
* Calculated total employees.
* Department-wise employee count.
* Work mode distribution (Office, Hybrid, Remote).
* Employee status analysis.
* Average salary by department.
* Top 10 highest-paid employees.
* Performance rating distribution.
* Average experience by department.
* Year-wise hiring trend.
* Total salary expense by department.
* Location-wise employee distribution.
* Top-performing employees.
* Average salary by work mode.
* Department-wise active employees.
* Employee experience categorization (Junior, Mid-Level, Senior).
* Top 5 highest-paying departments.
* Remote employees analysis.
* Employees with more than 10 years of experience.
* Dashboard KPI calculations (Total Employees, Active Employees, Average Salary, Average Performance Rating).

---

## 📊 Power BI Dashboard

The dashboard includes:

* KPI Cards
* Department-wise Employee Distribution
* Work Mode Analysis
* Employee Status Analysis
* Salary Analysis
* Performance Rating Analysis
* Experience Analysis
* Hiring Trend by Year
* Location-wise Employee Distribution
* Interactive Filters & Slicers

---

## 💡 Key Insights

* Identified departments with the highest workforce.
* Compared average salaries across departments.
* Analyzed employee distribution by work mode and location.
* Evaluated employee performance ratings.
* Examined workforce experience levels.
* Tracked hiring trends over the years.
* Highlighted the highest-paying departments.
* Measured key HR KPIs to support workforce planning.

---

## 🚀 Project Outcome

This project showcases an end-to-end HR analytics solution using **Python, SQL, and Power BI**. It demonstrates skills in data cleaning, exploratory data analysis, SQL-based business analysis, KPI creation, and interactive dashboard development to support data-driven HR decisions.
